criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  COPD diagnosis according to ATS/ERS criteria (post-bronchodilator FEV1 to FVC ratio <
             0.7);

          -  clinical stability, namely no acute exacerbation in the previous 4 weeks;

          -  clinical indication for low-dose computed tomography (LDCT) to investigate
             bronchiectasis, interstitial lung disease, or pulmonary hypertension.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnancy;

          -  patients with congenital or acquired immune deficit;

          -  patients with lung transplantation;

          -  patients under oxygen therapy;

          -  patients with diagnosis of asthma or other clinically relevant pulmonary disease other
             than COPD.
